## Courseware
/ confidentiality- Confidentiality is the assurance of that the information is accessible only to those authorized to have access. It controls include data classification, data encryption and proper disposal of equipment
/ Intigrity- the trustworthiness of data or resources in therms of preventing improper or unauthorized changes. 
/ Availability- Assurance that the systems responsible for delivering, storing, and processing information are accessible when required by the authorized users. 
/ Authenticity- Refers to the characteristic of a communication, document, or any data that ensures the quality of being genuine.Example-biometrics, smart cards
/ Non-repudiation- A guarantee that the sender of a message cannot later deny having sent the message and that the recipient cannot deny having received the message

/ Tactics, Techniques and Procedures(TTP)
/ Tactics is defined as the strategy adopted by an attacker to perform the attack from the beginning to the end.
/ Techniques is defined as technical methods used by an attacker to achieve intermediate results during the attack.
/ Procedures is defined as a systematic aproach adopt by threat actors to launch an attack
### study types of vulnerability
/ Classification of attacks- passive attack, active attack, close in attack, insider attack, distribution attacks

/ Information Warfare refers to the use of information and communication technologies to gain competitive advantages over an opponent
/ there are two types of information warefare- defensive and offensive
/ Defensive refers to all strategies and actions designed to defend against attacks on ICT assets.
/ Offensive refers to information warfare that involves attacks against the ICT assets of an opponent.
